The paper deals with secure transmission in the physical layer, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed scheme involves multiple antennas, which is a common feature in wireless communication networks, and hence the paper could also be classified under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization of beamforming vectors, which is a topic that falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which could also classify it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
